{
  "texts": [
    "For model card retrieval, REST overhead becomes substantial, indicating that transmitting large payloads through the REST layer incurs measurable latency beyond direct database access.",
    "Experiment II: Real WorldIn this second experiment we drive towards a more realistic scenario and do so in a few dimensions.",
    "As indicated earlier, Patra is unique in that it accumulates usage information about model inference servers.",
    "As such, model cards can grow to be sizeable.",
    "In this experiment we use synthetic model cards that are 13 MB in size (when formated as a JSON object).We further create a second client that is located on Jet-stream2 servers located in Hawaii (with the Patra server still residing in Indiana)."
  ]
}